Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Chief Librarian/Library Director Prince Rupert , BC Description Job Posting: Library Director (Chief Librarian)Prince Rupert Public Library / Wap Liitsx - House of ReadingLocation: Prince Rupert, British ColumbiaApplication Deadline: November 15, 2024About Prince RupertNestled on the northern coast of British Columbia, Prince Rupert is a vibrant community known for its stunning natural beauty, rich cultural heritage, and welcoming atmosphere. With access to breathtaking landscapes, outdoor recreational activities, and a diverse population, Prince Rupert offers a unique blend of urban amenities and small-town charm. The city is home to a variety of cultural events and festivals, making it an exciting place to live and work.Position SummaryThe Prince Rupert Public Library is seeking a dynamic and experienced Library Director (Chief Librarian) to lead our library operations. The successful candidate will be responsible for overseeing all aspects of library management, ensuring that services are delivered in alignment with the directives of the Board and the needs of our diverse community.The Library Director will play a crucial role in executing our Vision of promoting literacy, free access to information, and public engagement in a safe and inclusive environment. The ideal candidate will be dedicated to enhancing the lives of our community members through prudent selection of resources, innovative programming, and effective outreach.Key ResponsibilitiesAct as a liaison between the Library Board and staff, providing guidance on library management and policy development.Oversee collection development, ensuring a current and quality collection that meets community needs.Increase programming and enhance existing programs to better serve our patrons.Establish and strengthen community partnerships to enhance library objectives.Provide inclusive spaces and ensure the library is a welcoming place for all community members.Hire, train, and supervise staff and volunteers, fostering a collaborative and supportive work environment.Participate in the preparation of annual operating plans and budgets, ensuring financial accountability.Manage public services, including reference and readers’ advisory, programming, and community outreach.QualificationsMaster’s Degree in Library and Information Studies.Excellent written and verbal communication skills.Proficient computer skills and familiarity with automated library systems.Strong conflict resolution and problem-solving abilities.Administrative and supervisory experience.Commitment to patron service and community engagement.SalaryThe salary for this position ranges from approximately $91,676 to $108,682, depending on qualifications and experience.BenefitsThe Prince Rupert Public Library offers a competitive benefits package including professional development opportunities and up to 35 days of vacation annually. How to ApplyInterested candidates are invited to submit their resume and cover letter via email to boardchair@princerupertlibrary.ca by November 15, 2024. We thank all applicants for their interest in our organization; however, only short-listed applicants will be contacted.Join UsIf you are passionate about public service and committed to building relationships within a diverse community, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity to lead the Prince Rupert Public Library in achieving our vision and strategic goals. Compensation $91,676 - $108,692 Closes: 15 November, 2024 Prince Rupert Public Library Prince Rupert , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
